proteins, and dedicated genes that are continually protecting our bodies. Far more powerful than any medicine ever invented, the immune system plays a crucial role in our daily lives. We have found ways to harness these natural defenses to create breakthrough drugs and so-called immunotherapies that help us fight cancer, diabetes, arthritis, and many age-related diseases, and we are starting to understand whether activities such as mindfulness might play a role in enhancing our physical resilience. Written by a researcher at the forefront of this adventure, The Beautiful Cure tells a dramatic story of scientific detective work and discovery, of puzzles solved and mysteries that linger, of lives sacrificed and saved. With expertise and eloquence, Davis introduces us to this revelatory new understanding of the human body and what it takes to be healthy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aImmunity. 0aImmunology. 0aImmunotherapy. 7aMEDICAL / General.2bisacsh  aimmune system book, medical nonfiction books best sellers, medical nonfiction, immune system health books, how the immune system works, autoimmune disease book, medical breakthroughs book, immunologist, immune response, immune, immune system, immunity, immunotherapy, health, medicine, well-being, disease, autoimmune disease, cancer, diabetes, arthritis, virus, antiviral, germs, bacteria, antibody, cell, cellular, microbe, microbial, interferon, dendritic, receptor, cytokine, interleukin.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311068858040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226371146423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226371146/original  a978-3-11-068858-0  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles